(1) The Commission shall appoint a Director and a Deputy Director of the Commission .
The Commission shall appoint a Director and a Deputy Director of the Commission .
(2) The Director shall be— (a) the Secretary to the Commission ; (b) responsible for the management and administration of the Commission ; (c) a qualified advocate; (d) a full-time officer; and (e) responsible for the implementation of any matters referred to such Director by the Commission .
